questions.question_text_1: Let P and Q be two relations. Let D(P) be a decomposition of P based on a set M of functional dependencies. Let D(Q) be a decomposition of Q based on a set N of functional dependencies. It is known that one among D(P) and D(Q) is in 3NF and the other is in 2NF. In order to correctly classify D(P) and D(Q) as being in 3NF or 2NF,what is the MINIMAL test needed?
